Project Overview
This Digital Literacy Project was completed as part of the
CSE0001 course to develop essential skills required in the
digital world. The project is based on the role of a Student
Digital Ambassador, whose responsibility is to guide peers in
using digital tools safely and effectively.
The project consists of five tasks, each focusing on a different
aspect of digital literacy. These include creating an awareness
infographic, building a digital portfolio, exploring coding and
collaboration platforms, understanding email etiquette, and
learning about cybercrime and online safety.
Through this project, I gained practical experience in using
platforms like GitHub, LinkedIn, and Google Forms. It also
helped me understand the importance of responsible online
behaviour and professional communication. Overall, this
project enhanced my digital skills and prepared me to use
technology more effectively in academics and future career
opportunities.
