Task 4 – E-mail Etiquette
In this task, I learned the importance of professional communication
through email and responsible behaviour on social media. I wrote
two formal emails, one requesting an assignment extension and
another applying for a summer internship. While writing these
emails, I focused on maintaining a proper structure, including a clear
subject line, polite greeting, and formal tone.
I also created a checklist of social media do’s and don’ts to promote
responsible online behaviour among students. This helped me
understand how small mistakes in digital communication can create
misunderstandings or leave a negative impression. Overall, this task
improved my email writing skills and made me more aware of
maintaining professionalism in online interactions.
Task 5 -Cyber Crime Awareness
In this task, I explored the concept of cybercrime by studying a
phishing case related to bank KYC fraud. I learned how attackers
use fake messages and links to trick users into sharing sensitive
information such as OTPs and banking details. It was surprising to
see how easily people can fall into such traps due to lack of
awareness.
I also created a prevention checklist to help users stay safe online
by following simple practices like verifying links, using strong
passwords, and not sharing personal information. This task made
me more aware of online threats and the importance of digital
safety. I will be more cautious while using the internet and ensure
that I follow safe practices in the future.
